---
title: Pan-Seared Pork Chops with Shallot Thyme Pan Sauce, Peach Arugula Salad, and Couscous
description: Did you know that the average worker bee produces only 1/12 teaspoon of honey in a lifetime? This means we have a whole  lot of bees (and our brilliant chefs, of course) to thank for the sweet and herby pan sauce that’s generously drizzled on top  of tender pork. Oh—and there’s also a touch of the sweet stuff in the salad dressing, so expect to be licking your lips after every bite.
